{
 "name": "RPlog_Shape_of_My_Heart",
 "title": "The Shape of My Heart",
 "summary": "Unable to sleep aboard their ship, the scholar-musician Paul Nighman picks up Shenner's guitar in the dim cargo bay and quietly works out a long-abandoned song he wrote years ago, a haunting ballad about a gambler and the true shape of his heart. The music wakes the young Shenner, who lies transfixed in the dark rather than interrupt, until the song ends and she softly greets him. Moved that anyone wants to listen, Paul plays on at her urging and begins teaching the eager girl to finger-pick, delighting in how quickly she learns. Their lesson drifts into something tender and unspoken as Shenner confesses she will miss him if he leaves without her and lingers with a hand on his shoulder, before she shyly retreats to sleep and Paul, at peace, finally drifts into dreamless slumber.",
